name: Corsair International Boeing 747-400 Arrival at Calgary Airport
description:
What an awesome visitor! This Boeing 747-400 from French airline Corsair paid Calgary a visit, carrying a group of European tourists from Anchorage, Alaska. A passenger 747 is rare enough in Calgary, but I can't say I expected to see a Corsair one! This video includes the arrival on 17R, taxiing, some views of it parked on the apron, and then it later being towed to Apron II to await its departure later this week. Hope you enjoy this particularly rare catch, with ATC included!

Thanks for watching!
